        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:55AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 154 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Riviera, or near Sarita, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sarita and Kenedy County Sheriffs Office.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 712 and 714.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
